Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Remove the outer sleeve and the plastic film from the top of the @Dauphinoise Potatoes{350%grams} tray. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Pop the container onto one side of a large #baking tray{}.

Lay the @British Chicken Breasts{2} onto the other side of the baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

When there's ~{10%minutes} of roasting time left, pop the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%grams} onto a baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

Roast on the middle shelf, ~{10-12%minutes}.

When the chicken has ~{5%minutes} left, lay a slice of @Serrano Ham{2%slices} on top of each breast. Sprinkle the @Parmigiano Reggiano{20%grams} over the top.

Return to the oven for the remaining time, ~{5%minutes}.

When everything's ready, share the cheesy Serrano chicken between your plates.

Serve the potato dauphinoise and broccoli alongside.

Sprinkle the @Truffle Zest{1%sachet} over the dauphinoise. Scatter the @Toasted Flaked Almonds{15%grams} over the broccoli.

Drizzle the @Red Pepper Chilli Jelly{37%grams} over the chicken to finish.

Enjoy!